(1, 'Steel Panther', 'Ficha editorial armada para Steel Panther con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Ralph Saenz, Russ Parrish, Jess Harnell, Joe Lester (3)Contexto de catalogoHair / Glam Metal band from Los Angeles, CA formed in 2000.\r\n\r\nThe band has formerly been known as [a3173821], [a3972967] and [a1254183].\r\n\r\nThe band officially announced the departure of Lexxi Foxx on July 17, 2021 and found a replacement in Spyder, officially announced as a full-time member on September 20, 2022.\r\n\r\nLine-up:\r\nMichael Starr (Ralph Saenz) - singer\r\nSatchel (Russ Parrish) - lead guitar\r\nStix Zadinia (Darren Leader) - drums\r\nSpyder (Joe Lester) - bass\r\n\r\nPast member:\r\nLexxi Foxxx (Travis Haley) - bass (2000-2021)', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/m0R2TSy4BD7shuY4Y5bLj0QSKRqfYcGAqTYpYkHexCQ/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:483/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTE3ODgy/MTgtMTYzOTAzMTM1/Ni0yNjgwLmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-16 19:11:29', '2026-03-16 19:11:29'),
(2, 'Hell Yeah', 'Ficha editorial armada para Hell Yeah con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Jeff Death, Tyler H. Christ, Joe Kill &#039;EmContexto de catalogoUS punk band from Minneapolis, Minnesota.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/UdIxZ7K558q9oXH0-qoHon8wHmnix2rzkN8zlo-oYkE/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:450/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTE0MDMz/NDgtMTIzOTM3Nzgz/NC5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-16 19:23:54', '2026-03-16 19:23:54'),
(3, 'Warcry', 'Ficha editorial armada para Warcry con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Todd Burdette, Grant Kasten, Brad Boatright, Keith TestermanContexto de catalogoHardcore-punk band from Portland, Oregon.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/o3mP8HHYmglRBzBbvH1pSZhbOJW2yP1y9HOyOrvuzPU/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:432/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTc4MDg2/Ni0xNjAxMjc2MjYz/LTM3NDYuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-16 20:04:28', '2026-03-16 20:04:28'),
(4, 'KISS', 'Ficha editorial armada para KISS con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Bruce Kulick, Paul Stanley, Eric Singer, Ace FrehleyAlias / variaciones: &quot;Кисс&quot;, Kizz, The Kiss, キッスContexto de catalogoKISS was formed in Queens, New York (USA) in 1973 and retired 50 years later in 2023 after their final show in New York City. They played rock, hard rock, heavy metal and 1980s hair / glam metal. Their brand lives on through avatars and merchandise.\r\n\r\nEasily identified by its members\' face paint and flamboyant stage outfits, the group rose to prominence in the mid to late 1970s on the basis of their elaborate live performances, which featured fire breathing, blood spitting, smoking guitars, shooting rockets, levitating drum kits and pyrotechnics. Kiss has been awarded 24 gold albums to date. The band has sold more than 40 million albums in the United States, of which 19 million have been certified by the RIAA, and their worldwide sales exceeds 100 million albums.\r\n\r\nKiss trace their roots to Wicked Lester (2), a New York City based rock and roll band led by co-founders Gene Simmons and Paul Stanley. Wicked Lester, with its eclectic mixture of musical styles, never achieved any success. They recorded one album, which was shelved by Epic Records, and played a handful of live shows. Simmons and Stanley, feeling that a new musical direction was needed, abandoned Wicked Lester in 1972 and began forming a new group.\r\n\r\nIn late 1972, Simmons and Stanley came across an ad in the East Coast version of Rolling Stone placed by Peter Criss, a veteran drummer from the New York club scene, who was previously in bands called Lips and Chelsea. Criss auditioned for and joined the new version of Wicked Lester. The trio focused on a much harder style of rock than Wicked Lester played. Inspired by the theatrics of Alice Cooper and the New York Dolls, they also began experimenting with their image by wearing makeup and various outfits.\r\n\r\nIn early January 1973, the group added lead guitarist Ace Frehley who impressed the group on his first audition, where he showed up wearing two different sneakers, one red and one orange. A few weeks after Frehley joined, the Wicked Lester name was dropped and the band became Kiss.\r\n\r\nThe 1973–\'80 lineup of Paul Stanley (vocals and rhythm guitar), Gene Simmons (vocals and bass guitar), Ace Frehley (lead guitar and vocals), and Peter Criss (drums, percussion and vocals) is the most successful and identifiable. With their makeup and costumes, they took on the personas of comic book-style characters: Starchild (Stanley), The Demon (Simmons), Spaceman or Space Ace (Frehley), and Catman (Criss). The band explains that the fans were the ones who ultimately chose their makeup designs. Paul Stanley became the \"Starchild\" because of his tendency to be referred to as the \"starry-eyed lover\" and \"hopeless romantic.\" The \"Demon\" makeup reflected Simmons\'s cynicism and dark sense of humor, as well as his affection for comic books. Ace Frehley\'s \"Spaceman\" makeup was a reflection of his fondness for science fiction and supposedly being from another planet. Peter Criss\'s \"Catman\" makeup was in accordance with the belief that Criss had nine lives because of his rough childhood in Brooklyn. Because of creative differences, both Criss and Frehley left the group by 1982. The band\'s commercial fortunes  also waned considerably by that point.\r\n\r\nBuoyed by a wave of Kiss nostalgia in the 1990s, the band announced a reunion of the original lineup (with makeup) in 1996. The resulting Kiss Alive/Worldwide/Lost Cities/Reunion Tour was the top-grossing act of 1996 and 1997. Criss and Frehley have since left Kiss again and have been replaced by Eric Singer and Tommy Thayer, respectively. The band continues to perform with makeup, while Stanley and Simmons have remained the only two constant members.\r\n\r\nKiss has been named on many lists. They include Number 10 on VH1\'s \"100 Greatest Artists of Hard Rock\", 9th on \"The Greatest Metal Bands\" list by MTV, #1 on Hit Paraders\'s \"Top 100 Live Bands\", 56th on VH1\'s \"100 Greatest Artists Of All Time\" and 2nd on Digital Dream Door\'s \"Best Hair Metal Bands\".\r\n\r\nKiss was nominated for the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, ten years after becoming eligible. However, on December 15, 2009 it was announced that Kiss did not make it in. Five years later, they were finally inducted.\r\n\r\nThe band\'s name – which is often spelled in all capital letters – has been rumored to have many secret meanings, among them an acronym for \"Knights In Satan\'s Service\" and \"Kids In Satan\'s Service\".  The usual meaning though was always Keep It Simple Stupid and just Kiss instead of F**k according to Gene Simmons.\r\nThe bands logo is still altered/censored for german releases which has nothing to do with the band Kiss but their own history...since KISS members are mostly jewish, those rumours always have been ridiculous about the double S:s in the logo which always should be referred to as lightning S:s according to Ace Frehley.\r\n\r\nBecause of the ambiguity in the distinction between \"hard rock\" and \"heavy metal\", Kiss\' music has always been labeled one or the other. But shortly after the band\'s formation, critics called them \"thunderockers\". They also experimented in the disco/pop (Dynasty, Unmasked), art rock (Music from \"The Elder\") and grunge (Carnival of Souls: The Final Sessions) styles. Their music is described by Allmusic as \"a commercially potent mix of anthemic, fist-pounding hard rock, driven by sleek hooks and ballads powered by loud guitars, cloying melodies, and sweeping strings. It was a sound that laid the groundwork for both arena rock and the pop-metal that dominated rock in the late 80s.\"', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/PXRL-gv1bwTmjzz_llbgVd9r_KbIOXtBQXpVvAnlH18/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:912/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTE1MzA3/My0xNzYwNzIxNjI5/LTk2OTkuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-16 22:36:46', '2026-03-16 22:36:46'),
(5, 'Avenged Sevenfold', 'Ficha editorial armada para Avenged Sevenfold con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Brooks Wackerman, Matthew Charles Sanders, Dameon Ash, Jonathan SewardAlias / variaciones: A7X, Advanced Sevenfold, アヴェンジド・セヴンフォールドContexto de catalogoHeavy Metal/Metalcore band from Huntington Beach, California, formed in 1999.\r\nAbbreviated as A7X.\r\n\r\nCurrent Lineup:\r\nMatthew Sanders (M. Shadows) - Lead Vocals\r\nBrian Haner, Jr. (Synyster Gates) - Lead Guitar\r\nZachary Baker (Zacky Vengeance) - Rhythm Guitar\r\nJonathan Seward (Johnny Christ) - Bass\r\nBrooks Wackerman - Drums\r\n\r\nFormer Members:\r\nMatt Wendt - Bass\r\nJustin Meacham (Justin Sane) - Bass/Piano\r\nFrank Melcom (Dameon Ash) - Bass\r\nJames Sullivan (The Rev) - Drums/Piano/Co-Lead Vocals\r\nArin Ilejay - Drums', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/wQ_WQIjw4GRYwZT3ytW-0_FMCauLq6r8jS1RjhCTFtI/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:440/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI5OTg3/NC0xNjk2MzYwMjgy/LTM5NzkuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-17 09:14:48', '2026-03-17 09:14:48'),
(6, 'Annihilator', 'Ficha editorial armada para Annihilator con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Jeff Waters, Ray Hartmann, Dave Scott Davis, Coburn PharrAlias / variaciones: アナイアレイターContexto de catalogoCanadian speed/groove/thrash metal band formed in Ottawa, Ontario in 1984 and now based in Durham, England, UK. Formed in 1984 by the leader and only permanent member, vocalist, guitarist and bassist Jeff Waters.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/8cDxyUa0GM2xEeeVQ2VxgMcQxKH6Ix1A5fOXpxloDLs/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:333/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTM2ODc4/NC0xNTc5ODA5NTkz/LTM1OTMuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-17 23:51:59', '2026-03-17 23:51:59'),
(7, 'Rob Halford', 'Ficha editorial armada para Rob Halford con señales cruzadas de DiscogsGeneros: Two (2), Judas Priest, Bullring BrummiesAlias / variaciones: B. Halford, Bob Halford, Haford, HalfordContexto de catalogoEnglish heavy metal/hard rock singer-songwriter of the band [a252121]. Was also member of Abraxas, Athens Wood, Lord Lucifer, Thark. With drummer John Hinch he joined the band Hiroshima from 1972 to 1973. \r\n\r\nBorn August 25, 1951 in Birmingham. Brother of [a7440968] and [a2956532] drummer [a7436083].', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/D1CjNZG4j643SVGi7lQL7HZ5lHbQn45ngHpg0TLBgrQ/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:478/w:478/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI2MDY4/Ny0xNjI4MTA3ODcx/LTQ4MDguanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-17 23:53:55', '2026-03-17 23:53:55'),
(8, 'Napalm Death', 'Ficha editorial armada para Napalm Death con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Mick Harris, Justin K Broadrick, Lee Dorrian, Shane EmburyAlias / variaciones: N. D., N. Death, N.D., N.DeathContexto de catalogoFormed in Birmingham, UK in 1982, by Nik Bullen. Napalm Death were originally one of the bands that defined the UK hardcore thrash/punk sound of the mid-late 1980s, along with bands such as Extreme Noise Terror, Doom and Sore Throat. The band has gone through countless line-ups and many former members have gone on to become significant figures in a variety of musical scenes.\r\n\r\nAlthough their debut album \"Scum\" featured members Justin Broadrick (who was also a member of Fall of Because, the band that later became Godflesh, at the time) and Nik Bullen (later part of Scorn), the first stable line up consisted of Lee Dorrian (vocals), Bill Steer (guitar), Mick Harris (drums) and Shane Embury (bass).\r\n\r\nBy late 1989, Lee Dorrian, whose vocals epitomized the early Napalm Death sound, had left to form another band (doom metal band Cathedral) and focus on his label Rise Above. Bill Steer also left to concentrate on his other band, Carcass. Dorrian was replaced by former death metal band Benediction\'s vocalist Barney Greenway, and an American guitarist, Jesse Pintado, was recruited from fellow Earache label-mates Terrorizer. A short time later Mitch Harris from Las Vegas\' grindcore outfit Righteous Pigs joined as a second guitarist.\r\n\r\nMick Harris left the band in 1991 and has since been involved in a plethora of solo and joint projects/collaborations as Scorn, Lull, Quoit etc. He was replaced by Danny Herrera, an old friend of Jesse\'s from Los Angeles. This line-up lasted until 2004, when Jesse Pintado left the band. Currently the band consists of Barney Greenway, Mitch Harris, Shane Embury, John Cooke and Danny Herrera.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/ZZkONNon_qsclyc5BfsroIJGIlNs-t5isxzQviHxlL0/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:400/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTExNjE0/LTE2NjE0NzcyOTct/ODk0OC5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-18 22:46:22', '2026-03-18 22:46:22'),
(9, 'La Oreja De Van Gogh', 'Ficha editorial armada para La Oreja De Van Gogh con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Amaia Montero, Pablo Benegas, Xabier San Martin, Álvaro FuentesAlias / variaciones: LOVG, La Oreja deVan Gogh, Lodvg, ODVGContexto de catalogoSpanish pop rock group.\r\nFounded in 1996 in San Sebastian, Guipuzcoa, Spain.\r\n\r\nMembers:\r\nXabier San Martín - Keyboards, backing vocals\r\nPablo Benegas - Guitar \r\nÁlvaro Fuentes - Bass \r\nHaritz Garde - Drums \r\nAmaia Montero - Vocals\r\n\r\nSinger-songwriter Amaia Montero, member of the group since 1996, left in 2007 and was replaced by [a4568549]. Leire left in 2024. Amaia rejoined the band in 2025.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/hQlEh6SoI1Yfm4VTkseSEXG90ezrmSiiTlz3ZrjgHz0/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:600/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTU5MjM2/Mi0xNzYxMDc2NDc4/LTQ0NTYuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 13:50:25', '2026-03-19 13:50:25'),
(10, 'Jimi Hendrix', 'Ficha editorial armada para Jimi Hendrix con señales cruzadas de DiscogsGeneros: Johnny Jones And The King Casuals, The Jimi Hendrix Experience, Band Of GypsysAlias / variaciones: **, HENDRIX, Hendirx, HendixContexto de catalogoAmerican modern electric blues guitar virtuoso; lyricist, vocalist.\r\nBorn: 27 November 1942, Seattle, USA – Died: 18 September 1970, London, UK.\r\n\r\nA  self-taught guitarist, Hendrix began his musical career backing such R&B greats as Ike and Tina Turner, Sam Cooke, Wilson Pickett, Little Richard, The Isley Brothers, B.B. King and Curtis Knight. Brought to London from New York by former Animals bassist Chas Chandler, Hendrix quickly established himself as the brightest new star on the burgeoning progressive rock scene of late 1966. Along with bassist Noel Redding and drummer Mitch Mitchell he formed The Jimi Hendrix Experience.\r\n\r\nAfter a landmark appearance at the Monterey Pop festival, their debut album Are You Experienced was released in the US September 1967. The album, and its 1968 successors - Axis: Bold As Love and the seminal blues-oriented developments of Electric Ladyland - earned Hendrix international acclaim as a premier rock instrumentalist and innovator of his generation. A \'greatest hits\' collection, \"Smash Hits\" (1969), and an in-concert memento of his historic Monterey appearance, \"Otis Redding / Jimi Hendrix Experience at Monterey\" (1970), followed before his untimely death. A posthumous studio album, \"The Cry Of Love\", was released in January of 1971, followed by the double album soundtrack to the documentary film \"Jimi Hendrix\" in June of 1973.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/S8e2kk3LE1GDc6H4pHXiJZFqAv63zX75LC97n0qNskI/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:692/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTExMDU5/My0xNDQ5NTc4NDMw/LTY4MDcuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 13:59:53', '2026-03-19 13:59:53'),
(11, 'Black Label Society', 'Ficha editorial armada para Black Label Society con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Zakk Wylde, James LoMenzo, Craig Nunenmacher, Robert TrujilloAlias / variaciones: BLS, Zakk Wylde&#039;s BLS, Zakk Wylde&#039;s Black Label Society, ブラック・レーベル・ソサイアティContexto de catalogoAmerican heavy metal band formed in 1998 in Los Angeles by [a299759], also the guitarist of Ozzy Osbourne.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/L4r7tfXh894dMIzZXTuCOQu-QwDPIyKv4tsTmAqjR_c/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:600/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI5OTg2/My0xNjg0OTM5MTU4/LTgwMjYuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 14:04:09', '2026-03-19 14:04:09'),
(12, 'Seven Rock Radio', 'Ficha editorial armada para Seven Rock Radio con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Louis De Froment, Charles Schaaf, Pierre Pierlot, Emmanuel KrivineAlias / variaciones: &quot;Radio-Luxemburg&quot; Mit Seinem Orchester, Das Grosse Orchester Von Radio-Tele-Luxemburg, Das Grosse Symphonie Orchester Von RTL Radio Tele Luxemburg, Das Grosse Symphonie Orchester Von Radio-Tele-Luxemburg RTLContexto de catalogoSince its debut in 1933 under the aegis of Radio Luxembourg (RTL), the orchestra of the Grand Duchy, the Orchestre Philharmonique du Luxembourg (OPL) has been present all over Europe. Publicly administered since 1996, the OPL has been, since 2005, in residence at the Philharmonie Luxembourg.\r\nSince January 2012 both institutions have formed one and the same entity.\r\n \r\nThe acoustics of its residence, its long-standing connections with institutions like the Salle Pleyel in Paris and the Amsterdam Concertgebouw and with festivals like Musica (Strasbourg) and ArsMusica (Brussels) have contributed to making the OPL an orchestra renowned for the elegance of its sonority. Moreover, the precision and musicality of its music director, Emmanuel Krivine, and the orchestra’s close collaboration with first-rate musical personalities such as Evgeny Kissin, Julia Fischer, Jean-Yves Thibaudet and Jean-Guihen Queyras have consolidated the orchestra’s reputation. Its standing has been confirmed by an impressive list of prizes awarded for some twenty CDs, all released in the last seven years: Grand Prix Charles Cros, Victoires de la musique classique, Orphée d’Or de l’Académie du DisqueLyrique, Preis der Deutschen Schallplattenkritik, Télérama ffff, Pizzicato Excellentia, IRR Outstanding, BBC Music Choice, as well as several Diapasons d’Or, Choc du Monde de la Musique, Pizzicato Supersonic, Classica R10 and many others.\r\n \r\nNow in his seventh season, Emmanuel Krivine is the sixth music director of the OPL (after Henri Pensis, Louis de Froment, Leopold Hager, David Shallon and Bramwell Tovey). A disciple of Karl Böhm, Emmanuel Krivine holds to the ideal of a symphony orchestra, adapting to all available idioms and repertoires. This open attitude and the clarity of his readings have enabled the OPL to make a name for itself as «a transparent, elegant orchestra with a beautiful palette of colours» (Le Figaro), «free from anything flowery or nebulous but imbued with stylistic security and attuned to the specific qualities of each piece» (WDR). Alongside the classic and romantic repertoire, the orchestra’s programme reserves an important place for music of the twentieth and twenty-first centuries: works by Ivo Malec, Hugues Dufourt, Toshio Hosokawa, Klaus Huber, Bernd Alois Zimmermann, Helmut Lachenmann, Georges Lentz, Philippe Gaubert, Philip Glass, Michael Jarrell, Gabriel Pierné, Arthur Honegger and many others are regularly performed. The orchestra has also recorded the complete orchestral works of IannisXenakis.\r\n \r\nThe orchestra demonstrates its diversity with regular opera productions staged at the Grand Théâtre de Luxembourg; film concerts like «Live Cinema» in collaboration with the Cinémathèque de la Ville de Luxembourg; «Pops at the Phil» evenings with such stars as Patti Austin, Kurt Elling, Dionne Warwick, Maurane and Angélique Kidjo; open-air concerts with jazz and rock groups as part of the Fête de la Musique and so on. Soloists featured in the 2013/14 season include Martin Grubinger, Tine Thing Helseth, Vesselina Kasarova, Angelika Kirchschlager, Nikolaï Lugansky, Truls Mørk, Emmanuel Pahud, Alina Pogostkina, Baiba Skride, Alexandre Tharaud, Camilla Tilling and Arcadi Volodos, and conductors Richard Egarr, Susanna Mälkki, Juanjo Mena, Antonio Méndez, Tito Muñoz, Franck Ollu, Philip Pickett, Jonathan Stockhammer, Stefan Soltesz, Juraj Valčuha, Gast Waltzing and Ulrich Windfuhr.\r\n\r\nSince 2003, the orchestra’s own music education team «login:music» has organised concerts and workshops for schools, children and families; DVD productions as well as ‹pocket concerts› in schools and hospitals. In addition, it prepares school classes for subscription concerts with music appreciation workshops, and it arranges the «Dating:» cycle, which draws on actors and multi-media tools for encounters with the works of selected composers.\r\n \r\nTours take the orchestra to many music venues in Europe as well as in Asia and the USA. OPL concerts are regularly broadcast by Luxembourg radio 100,7 and internationally by the European Broadcasting Union (EBU).\r\n \r\nThe OPL is supported financially by the Ministry of Culture of the Grand Duchy and by the City of Luxembourg. Its partners are BGL BNP Paribas as well as Garage Arnold Kontz, Crédit Agricole Private Banking and P&T. Since December 2012 a cello made by Matteo Goffriller (1659–1742) called «Le Luxembourgeois» has been put at the OPL’s disposal by BGL BNP Paribas.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/qOSSIigTXYB8Wr7rV9Cz-mfKOi3eu0XEIvTYLSD2QiY/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:346/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTg2NTQx/Mi0xNTE2MTA3NTgy/LTc0NzQuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 14:08:41', '2026-03-19 14:08:41'),
(13, 'Thirty Seconds To Mars', 'Ficha editorial armada para Thirty Seconds To Mars con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Jared Leto, Solon Bixler, Shannon Leto, Tomo MiličevićAlias / variaciones: 12, 30 Sec To Mars, 30 Seconds 2 Mars, 30STMContexto de catalogoThirty Seconds to Mars (commonly stylized as 30 Seconds to Mars) is an American rock band from Los Angeles, California, formed in 1998. The band currently consists of brothers Jared Leto (vocals, guitars, bass guitar, keyboards) and Shannon Leto (drums, percussion). The band went through several former members including, Solon Bixler (guitars, vocals), Matt Wachter (bass guitar, keyboards, vocals), and Tomo Miličević (guitars, bass guitar, violin, keyboards, percussion).\r\n\r\nThe band\'s debut album, 30 Seconds to Mars (2002), was produced by Bob Ezrin and released to positive reviews but only to limited commercial success. The band achieved worldwide fame with the release of their second album A Beautiful Lie (2005), which received multiple certifications all over the world, including platinum in the United States. Their next release, This Is War (2009), showed a dramatic evolution in the band\'s musical style, as they incorporated experimental music as well as eclectic influences. The recording process of the album was marked by a legal dispute with record label EMI that eventually became the subject of the documentary film Artifact (2012). Thirty Seconds to Mars then moved to Universal Music and released the fourth album, Love, Lust, Faith and Dreams (2013), to critical and commercial success. It was followed by America (2018), which polarized critics upon release. As of September 2014, the band had sold over 15 million albums worldwide.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/KtVjhZDp5KxNT9F5-HSEJpKZ8pn1N-9DdJSkqu1hLiE/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:450/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTM5MDgy/OS0xNTM5NjI5MjM1/LTY2NjAuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 14:15:25', '2026-03-19 14:15:25'),
(14, 'Skid Row', 'Ficha editorial armada para Skid Row con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Rachel Bolan, ZP Theart, Sebastian Bach, Tony HarnellAlias / variaciones: Skidrow, Slid Row, Скид Роу, スキッド・ロウContexto de catalogoHair / Glam Metal (Heavy Metal)  band from Toms River, New Jersey (USA).\r\n\r\nCurrent Members:\r\nDave \"The Snake\" Sabo: Guitar, Backing Vocals (1986-1996, 1999-present)\r\nScotti Hill: Guitar, Backing Vocals (1987-1996, 1999-present)\r\nRachel Bolan: Bass, Backing Vocals (1986-1996, 1999-present)\r\nRob Hammersmith: Drums (2010-present)\r\n\r\nFormer Members:\r\nErik Grönwall: Lead Vocals (2022-2024)\r\nTony Harnell: Lead Vocals (2015)\r\nJohnny Solinger: Lead Vocals (1999-2015)\r\nSebastian Bach: Lead Vocals (1987-1996)\r\nRob Affuso: Drums, Percussion (1987-1996)\r\nPhil Varone: Drums (1999-2004)\r\nMatt Fallon: Lead Vocals (Original vocalist before Sebastian Bach)\r\nKeri Kelli: Guitar\r\nSteve Brotherton: Guitar\r\nKurtis Jackson: Guitar\r\nCharlie Mills: Drums\r\nTim DiDuro: Drums\r\nDave Gara: Drums (2004-2010)\r\nZP Theart: Lead Vocals (2016-2022)', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/zbTGYGY1Vg7YYzaSZ38Pw3ptRt3wP63ByFtg1VOSGE4/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:216/w:283/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI2MDY3/My0xMTA1ODYzNjEw/LmpwZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 14:15:38', '2026-03-19 14:15:38'),
(15, 'Rollins Band', 'Ficha editorial armada para Rollins Band con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Melvin Gibbs, Andrew Weiss, Chris Haskett, Theo Van EenbergenAlias / variaciones: Henry Rollins Band, Rollin&#039;s Band, Rolling Band, RollinsContexto de catalogoRollins Band was an American rock band led by singer and songwriter Henry Rollins. \r\n\r\nThe group started when Rollins and his friend Chris Haskett (guitar) teamed up with Gone (2)\'s rhythm section; Sim Cain (drums) and Andrew Weiss (bass). The band released the albums \"Life Time\" (1988), \"Hard Volume\" (1989) and \"The End of Silence\" (1992), before Weiss departed and was replaced by Melvin Gibbs. \r\n\r\nThey put out their fourth album \"Weight\" in 1994, which included the hit \"Liar\". Rollins got involved in a lawsuit with his former label, which was another factor in delaying the recording of the band\'s next album. Finally \"Come In and Burn\" was released in 1997, but by the end of the year the group had disbanded.\r\n\r\nIn 1998, Rollins got together with local LA group Mother Superior to try ideas on new songs. When it came time to tour, Rollins was advised to keep the \"Rollins Band\" name for the new group too. They went on to release the albums \"Get Some Go Again\" (2000), \"Nice\" (2001) and \"A Nicer Shade of Red\" (2001), before disbanding in 2003. \r\n\r\nThe Rollins / Haskett / Gibbs / Cain line-up also did a brief reunion in 2006.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/OMTFWXAZTz_O9VwvpW479xaE1QmduGskD8DAwbTMhR8/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:400/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTg3NjQ0/LTE2Nzc3OTkzMTct/OTM3MC5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 14:26:10', '2026-03-19 14:26:10'),
(16, 'Bon Jovi', 'Ficha editorial armada para Bon Jovi con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: David Bryan, Phil X, Jon Bon Jovi, Richie SamboraAlias / variaciones: B. Jovi, B.Jovi, Bon - Jovi, Bon-JoviContexto de catalogoAmerican rock band from New Jersey. \r\nAfter one of Jon Bongiovi\'s first demos, \'Runaway,\' became a hit on the Jersey airwaves, the young musician formed the group Bon Jovi in 1983. The group went on to become one of the most successful rock bands of the decade, earning a huge number of fans and numerous industry honors.\r\n\r\nThis profile is for Bon Jovi (the band). Solo releases can be found at Jon Bon Jovi (the individual).\r\n\r\nLineup:\r\nLead Vocals, Rhythm Guitar: Jon Bon Jovi.\r\nKeyboards: David Bryan.\r\nDrums & Percussion: Tico Torres.\r\nBass: Hugh McDonald.\r\nGuitars: Phil X\r\n\r\nFormer Members:\r\nBass (1983-1994): Alec John Such.\r\nLead Guitar,  Acoustic (6 &12 String) Guitars (1983-2013): Richie Sambora.\r\n\r\nNote: Hugh MacDonald occasionally plays Bass with Bon Jovi on albums and during live shows since 1994, but wasn\'t an official member until 2016.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/cNyeiVFAn8KRHPzmStXFJ9b2cl9jQJSHqIQ3n-K96RM/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:480/w:485/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTEyNDU0/MS0xMzYxNTUxOTA3/LTY2NDEuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 14:26:15', '2026-03-19 14:26:15'),
(17, 'Hellyeah', 'Ficha editorial armada para Hellyeah con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Roy Mayorga, Jerry Montano, Greg Tribbett, Chad GrayAlias / variaciones: Hellyeah!Contexto de catalogoHELLYEAH (formed in 2006 in Dallas, TX) is the Metal suprgroup featuring Mudvayne frontman Chad Gray, guitarist Greg Tribett also from Mudvayne, guitarist Tom Maxwell of Nothingface, bassist Jerry Montano another from Nothingface and drummer Roy Mayorga from Stone Sour.\r\n\r\nLine up changes:\r\nAfter group bass guitarist Jerry Montano was dismissed for violent behaviour, Bob Zilla was brought in to play bass guitar on tour for all of 2007. Roy Mayorga joined as the band\'s drummer following Vinnie Paul\'s death in 2018.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/FwWDPYRDJMCQL5TRmTBZnkcvdp5jhcVY01v9Dxr02KY/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:375/w:500/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTgxODg1/OS0xNDExNzY1NDA4/LTU0NjUuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 16:46:03', '2026-03-19 16:46:03'),
(18, 'Blind Guardian', 'Ficha editorial armada para Blind Guardian con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Hansi Kürsch, Marcus Siepen, Thomas Stauch, André OlbrichAlias / variaciones: ブラインド・ガーディアン, 瞽目守護神Contexto de catalogoPower/heavy metal band from Krefeld, Nordrhein Westfalen (Germany).\r\n\r\nBlind Guardian formed in 1984 as Lucifer\'s Heritage, then changed the name to Blind Guardian in 1986.\r\n\r\nTheir first two albums were essentially speed metal records with some power and thrash influences. Starting from their third album they started to add a much more melodic and \"epic\" feeling, with usage of choir and classical music influence.\r\n\r\nCurrent line-up:\r\nHansi Kürsch - vocals (1986-present), bass (1986-1995)\r\nAndré Olbrich - lead guitar (1986-present)\r\nMarcus Siepen - rhythm guitar (1987-present)\r\nFrederik Ehmke - drums (2005-present)\r\nJohan van Stratum - bass (2021-present)\r\n\r\nFormer members:\r\nThomas Stauch - drums (1987-2005)\r\n\r\nSession/live members:\r\nThomas Hackmann (studio) – backing vocals (1990–present)\r\nBilly King (2) (studio) – backing vocals (1992–present)\r\nOlaf Senkbeil (studio) – backing vocals (1997–present)\r\nMichael Schüren (live+studio) – keyboards, piano (1997–present)\r\nMatthias Ulmer (studio) – keyboards, piano (2007–present)\r\nBarend Courbois (live+studio) – bass (2012–present)\r\nOliver Holzwarth – bass (1997–2011)\r\nMathias Wiesner (studio) – keyboards, effects (1989–2002), bass (1992)\r\nRolf Köhler (studio) – backing vocals (1990–2007)\r\nAlex Holzwarth (live) – drums (2002–2003)\r\nPat Bender (studio) – keyboards, effects (2002–2006)\r\n\r\nOliver Holzwarth has never been added as a full time member so Hansi Kursch has the option of picking up bass duties again. Same thing for Barend Courbois.\r\nThomen Stauch left in 2005 after 20 years claiming dissatisfaction with the direction the band had taken on their, then, two most recent releases.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/Ha6Y8m-u53jR1es4zm_DSc48IDT9ZMoq7_-_raVR5Vk/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:399/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI2MjU3/Ny0xNjcxODM2NTMx/LTc1NjQuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 16:54:03', '2026-03-19 16:54:03'),
(19, 'L.A. Guns', 'Ficha editorial armada para L.A. Guns con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Mick Cripps, Phil Lewis, Tracii Guns, Axl RoseAlias / variaciones: L. A. Guns, L.A Guns, L.A. Gun, L.A. Guns (w/Paul Black)Contexto de catalogoL.A. Guns is an American rock band whose music is frequently associated with the L.A. glam metal scene which grew up around the Sunset Strip in the 1980s, in particular the sleaze rock subgenre. Guns N\' Roses, which once featured three of the original L.A. Guns members, was the most prominent exponent of this subgenre, generally preferring an anti-social image to elaborate make-up and costumes. \r\n\r\nL.A. Guns was formed in 1983 by guitarist Tracii Guns and drummer Rob Gardner.  Over the next couple years it would evolve into what became the original version of Guns n\' Roses.  Tracii Guns would depart that band in 1985 and launch a new version of L.A. Guns.  Throughout the years, a large number of musicians would pass through some version of the band (of which, at times, there have been two) and no single member would be consistently present at all times.  The band\'s longest-serving and best-known members are Tracii Guns, drummer Steve Riley (who joined the band in 1987 and is the closest thing to a constant member, having been in the band from 1987 until 1992, and again from 1994 until 2016), and vocalist Phil Lewis.  The L.A. Guns name was owned by both Tracii Guns and Steve Riley and both musicians have led their own versions of the band. Riley and Lewis led L.A. Guns from 1999 until 2016 while Guns had a second version of the band from 2006 to 2012.  In 2016, Lewis and Guns formed a new version of the band, while in 2018 Riley announced he had his own version (Riley\'s L.A. Guns) which included one-time bassist Kelly Nickels.  In 2020, Lewis and Guns filed a lawsuit against Riley over the trademark to the L.A. Guns name after which a settlement was reached in which Tracii Guns and Phil Lewis would retained ownership of the L.A. Guns name while Steve Riley would use the name \"Riley\'s L.A. Guns\" (Riley passed away in October of 2023 but his version of the band would continue until February 2025).', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/e_m4NjOW1TW0kRxt0E8FETl9b3sb9nsCsDO23ds6VkE/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:615/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI2MzIw/MS0xNTgxOTgwNDYx/LTUwMjkuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 16:54:06', '2026-03-19 16:54:06'),
(20, 'Marilyn Manson', 'Ficha editorial armada para Marilyn Manson con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Chris Vrenna, Tyler Bates, Wes Borland, Ginger FishAlias / variaciones: M. Manson, M.Manson, MAR1LYN MAN5ON, MMContexto de catalogoAmerican industrial metal and hard rock band which has gained notoriety for its extraordinary and outrageous contents, performance and media exposure.\r\nOriginally formed as [a229973] in 1989 in Florida, USA. It is commonly considered to be active as a solo project since 2007. \r\n\r\nThis is the band profile. For the person and band leader of the same name, see Marilyn Manson (2).\r\n\r\nCurrent members:\r\nMarilyn Manson (2) – vocals, guitar, percussion (1989–present)\r\nTyler Bates – guitar, backing vocals (2014–2015, 2017–2018, 2024–present)\r\nMatt Montgomery (2) – bass (2024–present)\r\nReba Meyers – guitar (2024–present)\r\nGil Sharone – drums (2014–2019, 2024–present)\r\n\r\nFormer members: (incl. previous \"The Spooky Kids\")\r\nJuan Alderete de la Pena – bass (2017–2020)\r\nPaul Wiley (2) – guitar (2014-2020)\r\nBrandon Pertzborn – drums (2019-2020)\r\nTwiggy Ramirez – bass (1993–2002, 2008–2009, 2014–2017), guitar (2009–2017)\r\nDaisy Berkowitz – guitar, programming (1989–1996; died 2017)\r\nZsa Zsa Speck – keyboards (1989)\r\nOlivia Newton Bundy – bass (1989)\r\nMadonna Wayne Gacy – keyboards, sampling, percussion (1989–2007)\r\nGidget Gein – bass (1989–1993)\r\nSara Lee Lucas – drums (1991–1995)\r\nGinger Fish – drums (1995–2004, 2006–2011)\r\nZim Zum – guitar (1996–1998)\r\nJohn 5 – guitar (1998–2004)\r\nTim Skold – bass (2002–2005), guitar (2006–2008)\r\nMark Chaussee – live guitar (2004–2005)\r\nRob Holliday – live bass (2007–2008), live guitar (2008)\r\nWes Borland – live guitar (2008–2009)\r\nAndrew Gerold – live bass (2009–2010)\r\nChris Vrenna – live drums (2004–2005), keyboards (2007–2011), live drums (2010–2011)\r\nFred Sablan – live bass (2010-2014)\r\nJason Sutter – live drums (2012-2014)', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/X8pFeysJ0MvHRpZVFdc08MwaAWlTGOUxq8MC6ISFEks/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:750/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTEyMjA4/LTE3Mzc3ODk0NjIt/NTYxNS5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 18:10:08', '2026-03-19 18:10:08'),
(21, 'Rata Blanca', 'Ficha editorial armada para Rata Blanca con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Gustavo Rowek, Danilo Moschen, Saul Blanch, Adrián BarilariContexto de catalogoArgentine Heavy Metal and Hard Rock band, founded in Buenos Aires in 1985 by guitarist Walter Giardino.\r\n\r\nWalter Giardino – Guitar (1985–1998, 2000–present)\r\nAdrián Barilari – Vocals (1989–1993, 2000–present)\r\nFernando Scarcella – Drums (2000–present)\r\nDanilo Moschen – Keyboards (2010–present)\r\nPablo Motyczak – Bass (2017–present)\r\n\r\nGustavo Rowek – Drums (1985–1997)\r\nYulie Ruth – Bass (1985)\r\nRodolfo Cava – Vocals (1985)\r\nGuillermo Sánchez – Bass (1985–1997, 2000–2017)\r\nSergio Berdichevsky – Rhythm Guitar (1985–1997)\r\nSaúl Blanch – Vocals (1986–1987, 1988–1989)\r\nCarlos Périgo – Vocals (1988)\r\nShito Molina – Vocals (1988)\r\nLowi Novello – Vocals (1988)\r\nHugo Bistolfi – Keyboards (1989–1993, 2000–2010)\r\nJavier Retamozo – Keyboards (1993–1998)\r\nMario Ian – Vocals (1993–1997)\r\nGabirel Marián – Vocals (1997–1998)', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/VKkn6_acToQC0-Si5vSb15rr_rXkFpsia0CG1o5kUuE/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:362/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTE2NjUw/OTktMTY4MjM4OTA0/Ni04NjA4LmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-19 18:10:11', '2026-03-19 18:10:11'),
(22, 'Charly García', 'Ficha editorial armada para Charly García con señales cruzadas de DiscogsGeneros: Serú Girán, Sui Generis (4), La Máquina De Hacer PájarosAlias / variaciones: C. A. Garcia, C. G., C. Garcia, C. GarcíaContexto de catalogoArgentine musician and composer. Considered one of the greatest Argentine rock artists.\r\nBorn 23 October 1951.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/C5OVWiHmlZyhiQOZb1dS_KV2QyRf1xWQ3BN8nQcxRwg/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:902/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTkwODY1/MS0xNTM0ODYzMTky/LTc4OTQuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 13:10:28', '2026-03-20 13:10:28'),
(23, 'Fleetwood Mac', 'Ficha editorial armada para Fleetwood Mac con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Stevie Nicks, Neil Finn, Mike Campbell, Christine McVieAlias / variaciones: A.F. Mac, F. Mac, FM, FMACContexto de catalogoFounded in London in July 1967 (by ex-Bluesbreakers members, Peter Green and Mick Fleetwood), \"Peter Green\'s Fleetwood Mac\" instantly became a major force in the UK blues scene, along with their eponymous first album. Following \"Mr. Wonderful\" & \"Then Play On\" the driving force of Peter Green had deteriorated as he lapsed into a personal crisis by 1970. The group reorganized, under the leadership of Fleetwood, and slowly took on a new direction - away from the blues and into the mainstream of international popularity, known simply as Fleetwood Mac.\r\n\r\nMember/Dates:\r\nPeter Green (guitar, vocals, 1967-70)\r\nMick Fleetwood (drums, 1967-1995, 1997-present)\r\nJohn McVie (bass, 1967-1995, 1997-present)\r\nJeremy Spencer (guitar, vocals, 1967-71)\r\nBob Brunning (bass, 1967)\r\nDanny Kirwan (guitar, 1968-72)\r\nChristine McVie (vocals, piano, accordion, 1970-1995, 1997-1998, 2014-2022)\r\nBob Welch (guitar, vocals, 1971-74)\r\nBob Weston (guitar, 1973-74)\r\nDave Walker (guitar, vocals, 1973)\r\nDoug Graves (keyboards, 1974)\r\nLindsey Buckingham (guitar, vocals, piano, 1975-87, 1993, 1997-2018)\r\nStevie Nicks (vocals, 1974–1991, 1993, 1997-present)\r\nBilly Burnette (guitar, vocals, 1990-94)\r\nRick Vito (guitar, 1990-91)\r\nDave Mason, (guitar, vocals, 1993-94)\r\nBekka Bramlett (vocals, 1993-94)\r\nMike Campbell (lead guitar, vocals, 2018–present)\r\nNeil Finn, (vocals, rhythm guitar, 2018–present)\r\n\r\nInducted into Rock And Roll Hall of Fame in 1998 (Performer)', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/7DEGJ9c_dBLM19IiLux-yTm_Ru33-dKSr9FDbByJmGs/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:722/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTQ3MzMz/LTE1NjY1NjE1NDkt/MzM1NS5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 13:25:44', '2026-03-20 13:25:44'),
(24, 'David Bowie', 'Ficha editorial armada para David Bowie con señales cruzadas de DiscogsAlias / variaciones: 2-1, B. Bowie, Boh Oui, BowieContexto de catalogoBritish pop/rock singer, musician, songwriter, and actor.\r\n\r\nBorn: 8 January 1947 in Brixton, London, England, UK.\r\nDied: 10 January 2016 in Manhattan, New York City, USA (aged 69).\r\n\r\nBowie is recognized as one of the most respected contemporary musicians of his period. He was a leading figure in the music industry and is considered one of the most influential musicians of the 20th century.\r\nInducted into Rock And Roll Hall of Fame in 1996.\r\n\r\nFor a list of all band and group involvement, please see [a1240431].', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/Nc1FSm4J27mP2ZdvaR9uluSd7T8Vhn6uf5jw2SHdI3I/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:591/w:598/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTEwMjYz/LTEzNDA4NzIyMTMt/OTc4MC5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 14:16:59', '2026-03-20 14:16:59'),
(25, 'Lenny Kravitz', 'Ficha editorial armada para Lenny Kravitz con señales cruzadas de DiscogsGeneros: B.M.U., The Plastic Ono Band, Peace ChoirAlias / variaciones: Kravitz, Kravitz L, Kravitz Leonard. A., Kravitz, LennyContexto de catalogoAmerican singer-songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, record producer, actor, photographer and arranger, born May 26, 1964 in New York City, New York, USA. He was married to Lisa Bonet from 1987 to 1993. Father of Zoë Kravitz.\r\nFan club: [a6742372]', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/w3DeAO3qGCI4omRGYQn5a0woW6uoLB_oGB6Znj5sd-E/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:600/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTYzMzMy/LTE0MTIwMTU0NjIt/MzQ5Ni5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 14:17:05', '2026-03-20 14:17:05'),
(26, 'Ángeles Del Infierno', 'Ficha editorial armada para Ángeles Del Infierno con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Robert Álvarez, Juan Gallardo, Manu García, Santi RubioAlias / variaciones: Ángeles Del InfiernoContexto de catalogoSpanish hard rock band formed in 1978 in Lasarte (Guipúzcoa, Basque Country)\r\nThey premiered their first long play (LP) opening for [a84752] in front of more than 15,000 people although they had already alternated with bands like [a233658] in 1982 and [a263589] in 1983, demonstrating a 200% performance live, which made their presentations awaken an unusual expectation.\r\n\r\n[a1226755] first album \"302764\" is commonly considered as the bible of Heavy Metal in Spanish. On this album we find great classics like “Maldito Sea Tu Nombre”, “Rocker”, “El Principio Del Fin”, “Sombras En La Oscuridad”, etc.\r\nAlso “Fuera De La Ley”, “666”, “Con Las Botas Puestas”, “Pensando En Ti”, “Al Otro Lado Del Silencio”, “Si Tu No Estas Aquí” until his most recent work \"691278\", they have earned them several multi-platinum albums and they continue to tour non-stop before thousands and thousands of fans in each city/country where they perform!\r\n\r\nWith more than 40 years of career on stages, roads, studios, festivals, etc... Angeles Del Infierno is the Hispanic group of this genre that has obtained the most success internationally and is managing to sustain itself for the longest time.\r\n\r\nThey were the first to arrive and they did so as stars.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/eTGtfePhULAw775gL8IDJ4xJfuj6UJY2yyOqZKdQenM/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:316/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTEyMjY3/NTUtMTY5MjQ5NzIz/MS02MTg4LmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 15:31:53', '2026-03-20 15:31:53'),
(27, 'Europe', 'Ficha editorial armada para Europe con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Kjell Lövbom, John Norum, John Levén, Marcel JacobAlias / variaciones: Europa, Europe Mark I, Europe Mark II, Europe Mark IIIContexto de catalogoSwedish hair / glam metal (Heavy Metal) band from Upplands Väsby, Stockholm.\r\n\r\nEurope formed in 1979. The band rose to international fame in the 1980s with its third album, 1986\'s The Final Countdown, which sold over three million copies in the United States. Europe sold over 23 million albums worldwide. Europe went on hiatus in 1992, reunited temporarily for a one-off performance in Stockholm on New Year\'s Eve 1999 and announced an official reunion in 2003.\r\n\r\nIn September 1985, Europe was approached by an executive from Epic Records. They helped Europe start the recording of its next album with Journey producer Kevin Elson. The result was The Final Countdown. Released on 26 May 1986, the album gave the band its international breakthrough, was certified Triple Platinum in the USA.\r\n\r\nIn mid-2017 Europe announced their eleventh studio album, titled 1254094. The album was released on October 20th via CD with bonus DVD and digital download.\r\n\r\nEurope Mark I:\r\n- Joey Tempest : Vocals, Keyboards, Acoustic Guitar\r\n- John Norum : Guitars\r\n- John Levén : Bass\r\n- Tony Reno : Drums, Percussion\r\n\r\nEurope Mark II:\r\n- Joey Tempest : Vocals\r\n- John Norum : Guitars\r\n- John Levén : Bass\r\n- Mic Michaeli : Keyboards\r\n- Ian Haugland : Drums, Percussion\r\n\r\nEurope Mark III:\r\n- Joey Tempest : Vocals\r\n- Kee Marcello : Guitars\r\n- John Levén : Bass\r\n- Mic Michaeli : Keyboards\r\n- Ian Haugland : Drums, Percussion\r\n\r\nEurope Mark II (reunited):\r\n- Joey Tempest : Vocals\r\n- John Norum : Guitars\r\n- John Levén : Bass\r\n- Mic Michaeli : Keyboards\r\n- Ian Haugland : Drums, Percussion', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/JXAogsxrYwUFHPRbqIdsid-Q3EIzMLjK0XmUDINBzWg/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:198/w:300/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI1MTk1/MC0xMTA0NjYwNzYx/LmpwZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 16:14:48', '2026-03-20 16:14:48'),
(28, 'Los Mentas', 'Ficha editorial armada para Los Mentas con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Juan Olmedillo, Richard Blanco, Carlos Aray, Héctor ParedesContexto de catalogoVenezuelan rock-rockabilly-surf-punk band formed at 1998', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/yAiYjEZLWn34fvP_7cz49KdG4tjTT5I23ATD1FwgQgY/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:400/w:400/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTE5ODk0/MTMtMTUzNDkxNzEx/MC0xMzE4LmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 16:14:54', '2026-03-20 16:14:54'),
(29, 'ANDREA UROBOROS', 'Ficha editorial armada para ANDREA UROBOROS con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Jose Martínez Arroyo, Sergio Cisneros Anguita, Juan Flores &quot;Chino&quot;, José Rubio JiménezContexto de catalogoSpanish heavy/folk metal band formed by [a2435090].', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/HrXl7ZqoQdDMcWPuiNa2HXWTfhViX7xCfme2c8mu7xc/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:600/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTYyMjcx/NDItMTUxNTIwMDMx/My04NjIxLmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 18:14:17', '2026-03-20 18:14:17'),
(30, 'Phobia', 'Ficha editorial armada para Phobia con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Raymond Herrera, Danny Walker (2), Shane McLachlan, Dino SommeseAlias / variaciones: PhobiaContexto de catalogoGrindcore band from Mission Viejo, California, United States. Started in 1990.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/mK9Rc8iHVxhM-qZNMMS5uRi8oxP4XvjMg6uJaREq5qg/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:600/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI3NjMz/Ni0xNTUxNTUwMzIz/LTEzNDAuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 21:07:06', '2026-03-20 21:07:06'),
(31, 'Bad English', 'Ficha editorial armada para Bad English con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: John Waite, Ricky Phillips, Jonathan Cain, Neal SchonAlias / variaciones: バッド・イングリッシュContexto de catalogoAmerican/British hard rock supergroup formed in 1988, reuniting keyboardist Jonathan Cain with singer John Waite and bassist Ricky Phillips, his former bandmates in The Babys.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/ueYE7E30_RGSr2Hxzn7JkEqaB9Yw6Io52TVP_f3QoTs/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:308/w:250/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI1NDQw/NC0xMjQzODQ5ODAy/LmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-20 21:07:11', '2026-03-20 21:07:11'),
(32, 'Bob Marley & The Wailers', 'Ficha editorial armada para Bob Marley &amp; The Wailers con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Marcia Griffiths, Bob Marley, Rita Marley, Judy MowattAlias / variaciones: (Bob Marley) &amp; The Wailers, (Bob Marley) And The Wailers, ...Bob Marley And The Wailers, B. Marley &amp; The WailersContexto de catalogoJamaican reggae band fronted by [a41441] but initially formed as [a52145] vocal group, with peter tosh & bunny wailer, then adding the rhythm section of the upsetters ([a386410] & [a386407]). In 1974, after Peter Tosh and Bunny Wailer departures, producer chris blackwell renamed the group Bob Marley & The Wailers (even if some previous records were released with this name) and marketed it as a rock band (vocalist + instrumental band). After Bob Marley\'s death in 1981, The Wailers continue to record with some artists like alpha blondy, Joe Yamanaka, Donald And Lulu Davidson or Winston Jarrett. Some members of The Wailers formed the wailers band in 1989.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/Nd1m6BuNEAhOBQ28zjbZ2YyL41EVzPbs2um0YPy4Ggo/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:399/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTIxNzY0/LTE2OTUyNTE0MTEt/MjY1OS5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-21 10:12:23', '2026-03-21 10:12:23');
INSERT INTO `radio_artists` (`id`, `name`, `biography`, `editorial_summary`, `image_path`, `featured_facts`, `milestones`, `related_artists`, `official_links`, `last_verified_at`, `source`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(33, 'Deep Purple', 'Ficha editorial armada para Deep Purple con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Joe Satriani, Steve Morse, Roger Glover, Ian PaiceAlias / variaciones: &quot;Дип Пэрпл&quot;, &quot;Дип Пёрпл&quot;, D. P., D. PurpleContexto de catalogoHard Rock band from England, United Kingdom.\r\n\r\nThe band formed in 1968. Along with Led Zeppelin and Black Sabbath, they are considered to be among the pioneers of heavy metal and modern hard rock, although some band members believe that their music cannot be categorised as belonging to any one genre. They were once listed by the Guinness Book of World Records as \"the loudest pop group\", and have sold over 100 million albums worldwide. Deep Purple were ranked #22 on VH1\'s Greatest Artists of Hard Rock programme.\r\n\r\nThere has been a Deep Purple band in existence since the late 60s, apart from the eight years between 1976 when Mark IV split up and 1984 when Mark II reformed. \r\n\r\nDeep Purple were inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2016.\r\n\r\nThey went through different line-ups through their history: \r\nMark I (1968-69): \r\nVocals: Rod Evans, \r\nGuitar: Ritchie Blackmore, \r\nBass: Nick Simper, \r\nKeyboards: Jon Lord. \r\nDrums: Ian Paice. \r\n\r\nMark II (1969-73, 1984-89, 1992-93): \r\nVocals: Ian Gillan, \r\nGuitar: Ritchie Blackmore, \r\nBass: Roger Glover, \r\nKeyboards: Jon Lord. \r\nDrums: Ian Paice. \r\n\r\nMark III (1973-75): \r\nVocals: David Coverdale, \r\nGuitar: Ritchie Blackmore, \r\nBass and vocals: Glenn Hughes, \r\nKeyboards: Jon Lord. \r\nDrums: Ian Paice. \r\n\r\nMark IV (1975-76): \r\nVocals: David Coverdale, \r\nGuitar: Tommy Bolin, \r\nBass and vocals: Glenn Hughes, \r\nKeyboards: Jon Lord. \r\nDrums: Ian Paice. \r\n\r\nMark V (1989-92): \r\nVocals: Joe Lynn Turner, \r\nGuitar: Ritchie Blackmore, \r\nBass: Roger Glover, \r\nKeyboards: Jon Lord. \r\nDrums: Ian Paice. \r\n\r\nMark VI (1993-94): \r\nVocals: Ian Gillan, \r\nGuitar: Joe Satriani, \r\nBass: Roger Glover, \r\nKeyboards: Jon Lord. \r\nDrums: Ian Paice. \r\n\r\nMark VII (1994-2002):\r\nVocals: Ian Gillan, \r\nGuitar: Steve Morse, \r\nBass: Roger Glover, \r\nKeyboards: Jon Lord. \r\nDrums: Ian Paice. \r\n\r\nMark VIII (2002-2022):\r\nVocals: Ian Gillan, \r\nGuitar: Steve Morse, \r\nBass: Roger Glover, \r\nKeyboards: Don Airey. \r\nDrums: Ian Paice. \r\n\r\nMark IX (2022-current):\r\nVocals: Ian Gillan, \r\nGuitar: Simon McBride, \r\nBass: Roger Glover, \r\nKeyboards: Don Airey. \r\nDrums: Ian Paice.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/53Qt8vZl-wO-5m1ENErFuRa8yyPYcnGJopin6mllQWQ/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:572/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTE3MDM1/NS0xMzE4MDgwOTAx/LmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-21 11:10:13', '2026-03-21 11:10:13'),
(34, 'Soul Asylum', 'Ficha editorial armada para Soul Asylum con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: David Pirner, Michael Bland, Sterling Campbell, Winston RoyeAlias / variaciones: Soul Sylum, Soul System, 神魂顛倒合唱團, 소울 어사일럼Contexto de catalogoSoul Asylum is an American alternative rock band formed in 1981 in Minneapolis, Minnesota, best known for the Grammy-winning 1993 hit \"Runaway Train\". The band was originally called [a1422017], with a lineup consisting of Dave Pirner, Dan Murphy, Karl Mueller, and Pat Morley. They changed their name to Soul Asylum in 1983. Morley was replaced by Grant Young in 1984. The band recorded three albums with Twin/Tone Records and two with A&M Records, with little commercial success. In 1992, they released the triple-platinum album Grave Dancers Union, featuring \"Runaway Train\". The band played at the inauguration of President Bill Clinton early the next year. They also scored a platinum record with the album Let Your Dim Light Shine three years later.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/uix2tK5cOwwLoFtN2uJ7H-l6D5YgstmM3J6-i8xx07U/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:398/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI1MTk0/MS0xNjI0MDQ2Mjgw/LTE2OTEuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-21 19:03:26', '2026-03-21 19:03:26'),
(35, 'My Chemical Romance', 'Ficha editorial armada para My Chemical Romance con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Gerard Way, James Dewees, Frank Iero, Ray ToroAlias / variaciones: Chemical Romance, MCR, My Chemical Romance., My Chemical RomaneContexto de catalogoMy Chemical Romance is an American rock band from New Jersey, formed in November 2001. The band consists of lead vocalist Gerard Way, guitarists Ray Toro and Frank Iero, and bassist Mikey Way. Shortly after forming, the band signed to Eyeball Records and released their debut album I Brought You My Bullets, You Brought Me Your Love in 2002. They signed with Reprise Records the next year and released their major label debut Three Cheers for Sweet Revenge in 2004; the album was a commercial success, and was awarded platinum status a little over a year later. The band eclipsed their previous success with their 2006 concept album, The Black Parade, which gained generally favorable reviews among music critics. They have since finished recording their fourth studio album, Danger Days: The True Lives of the Fabulous Killjoys, which was released in November 2010. On March 22, 2013, the band announced their break up. On October 31, 2019, the band announced a reunion, with an opening show in Los Angeles.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/33riI2JfENvqcZpSuWNedaW_M_3vUimaBIlJXrjEA_Q/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:926/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTMxOTQw/Ni0xNjUyNDE3NDE1/LTc3MDEuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-21 19:03:31', '2026-03-21 19:03:31'),
(36, 'La Pestilencia', 'Ficha editorial armada para La Pestilencia con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Mauricio Montoya, Juan Carlos Gomez, Dilson Díaz, Germán VillaContexto de catalogoHardcore / Punk / Rock\r\nColombia / Los Angeles, California, United States.\r\nEMI / Capitol / En discográficas grandes o multinacionales.\r\nSince 1986', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/VyYjm9Vz42sECqwlukMTA4d3nkTyEdWCKFsJm1m5TBg/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:600/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTQzMDQ2/Mi0xNDkyMzY5MjE3/LTI2NjEuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-22 04:31:22', '2026-03-22 04:31:22'),
(37, 'Burning', 'Ficha editorial armada para Burning con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Ramiro Penas, Arturo Terriza, Carlos Guardado, Edu PinillaAlias / variaciones: J. A. Martín/J. Casas/J. A. Cifuentes/E. PérezContexto de catalogoSpanish Rock band based in Madrid. Founded in 1974 by José Casas \"Pepe Risi\" (guitar), Enrique Pérez \"Quique\" (bass), J.A. Martín \"Toño\" (vocals), and J. A. \"Johnny\" Cifuentes (keyboards). They had three drummers on their first years (Ernesto \"Tito\" Estepa 1974-76; Ildefonso García Alvarez \"Fonso\" 1976-78; and Roberto Oltra \"Teto\" 1978-79). In  1979 the original line-up is broken when Quique leaves the band, and later in 1983 Toño left them too, remaining the band as Pepe Risi-Johnny with backing musicians until Risi\'s death in 1997. The band went on with more backing musicians with Johnny as the only founder member until 2019. Then Johnny Cifuentes released in 2020 a solo album as Johnny Burning (3) \"Hagámoslo\".\r\n\r\nOriginal lineup:\r\nToño Martín - vocals (1974-1983). Died in 1991.\r\nPepe Risi - guitar (1974-1997). Died in 1997.\r\nQuique Pérez - bass (1974-1979).\r\nJohnny Cifuentes - keyboard (1974-2019).\r\nErnesto Estepa Tito - drums (1974-1976).\r\n\r\nThe final 2019 line up of Burning was:\r\nJohnny Cifuentes - vocals, piano and keyboard) (since1974)\r\nCarlos Guardado  - bass (since 1987)\r\nEduardo Pinilla - guitar (since 1992)\r\nKacho Casal - drums (since 1997)\r\nMiguel Slingluff - saxo (since 2006).\r\nNico Álvarez - guitar (since 2014).\r\n\r\nIn between members:\r\nIldefonso García Fonso - drums (1976-1978).\r\nRoberto Oltra Teto - drums (1978-1979).\r\nÁngel Lito - drums (1979-1983).\r\nManolo Fernández - bass (1980-1983).\r\nMiguel Slingluff - sax (1980-1990).\r\nEloy García - bajo (1984).\r\nArturo Terriza - drums (1984-1986). Died in 1996\r\nEsteban Cabezos Deville - bass (1985).\r\nSuso Rey - bass (1986).\r\nLolo Beceiro - drums (1986).\r\nNacho Blanco - drums (1987-1997).\r\nLorenzo Azcona Pájaro - sax (1990-1997).\r\nPitu (2010-2014).\r\n\r\nCollaborators:\r\nPichacho - guitar (1979, 1986).\r\nPablo Vázquez - trumpet (1986).\r\nFernando Fernández - harmonica (1989, 1991, 2002).\r\nJaime Asúa - guitar (1990-1991).\r\nJavier Mora - Keyboards (1991).\r\nMiguel Slingluff Maykol - sax (2006-).', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/BTPxtUuHqSpgCfbBl3xYapFow_mOjenGqPquB_yvTU4/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:548/w:430/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTEyMjQ5/ODQtMTI1NTMwMzY5/My5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-22 04:31:27', '2026-03-22 04:31:27'),
(38, 'Nirvana', 'Ficha editorial armada para Nirvana con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Dave Grohl, Chad Channing, Dan Peters, Dale CroverAlias / variaciones: Nervana, Nirvahna, Nirvanna, 涅盤Contexto de catalogoRock/grunge band from Aberdeen, Washington, USA, formed in 1987. Emerging from the Seattle grunge scene of the late 1980s/early 1990s, Nirvana was a power trio of musicians who brought a new aesthetic to the rock scene of the time. They had already released their debut LP \"13773\" with Sub Pop, but their 1991 major-label debut for DGC/Geffen Records, \"13814\" broke the band and grunge into the mainstream of America. Singer/guitarist Kurt Cobain\'s death by suicide in April 1994 brought the band to an end.\r\n\r\nThe band\'s names in a chronological order:\r\nSkid Row (6) (start (March 1987) - June 26, 1987)\r\nPen Cap Chew (2) (June 27, 1987 - August 8, 1987)\r\nBliss (108) (August 9, 1987 - January 1988)\r\nTed Ed Fred (January 1988 - March 18, 1988)\r\nNirvana (March 19, 1988 - end (April 5, 1994))\r\n\r\nIt was rumoured that there were two other short-used band names before Nirvana: Throat Oyster and Windowpane (no official proofs for it though)\r\n\r\nFinal line-up:\r\nKurt Cobain – lead guitar, lead vocals (March 1987 (start)–April 5, 1994 (end); died April 5, 1994)\r\nKrist Novoselic – bass (March 1987 (start)–April 5, 1994 (end)), accordion (1993–1994)\r\nDave Grohl – drums, backing vocals (September 25, 1990–April 5, 1994 (end))\r\nPat Smear – rhythm guitar, backing vocals (September 23, 1993–April 5, 1994 (end))\r\n\r\nFormer members:\r\nAaron Burckhard – drums (March 1987 (start)–October 1987)\r\nDale Crover – drums (December 1987–February 15, 1988, August 10, 1990–August 25, 1990), backing vocals (1988)\r\nDave Foster (14) – drums (February 16, 1988–May 24, 1988)\r\nChad Channing – drums (May 25, 1988–June 1990)\r\nJason Everman – rhythm guitar, backing vocals (February 5, 1989–July 19, 1989)\r\nDan Peters – drums (June 1990–August 1990, September 1990–September 24, 1990)\r\n\r\nTouring musicians:\r\nRobert Roth – guitar (August 1989) (*rehearsals only)\r\nBen Shepherd – guitar (September 26, 1989-September 28, 1989) (*soundcheck only)\r\nJohn Duncan – guitar (July 15, 1993–July 31, 1993)\r\nLori Goldston – cello (July 15, 1993–January 8, 1994)\r\nMelora Creager – cello (February 5, 1994–April 5, 1994 (end))\r\n\r\nSession musicians:\r\nMark Pickerel – drums (1989)\r\nKirk Canning – cello (1991)\r\nKera Schaley – cello (1993)\r\n\r\nLive guest musicians:\r\nTony Poukkula – guitar (1987)\r\nRyan Aigner – guitar (1987) (also was the band\'s first manager)\r\nAntony Hodgkinson (aka Dancing Tony) – dancing (1990, 1991, 1992)', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/S_HB3FZR5TTcRyjBqlnUQpF_WgF-i9iSqcMTQGdwB6M/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:609/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTEyNTI0/Ni0xNTAxMjg1MjAw/LTMwNTguanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-23 09:13:27', '2026-03-23 09:13:27'),
(39, 'Masacre', 'Ficha editorial armada para Masacre con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Alex Oquendo, Mauricio Montoya, Alejandro Saldarriaga, Juan Carlos GomezAlias / variaciones: Masacre Team, Massacre, The Bad ButcherContexto de catalogoDeath Metal band from Medellin-Colombia, founded in 1988.\r\n\r\nThe name \"The Bad Butcher\" was used by the label Metal Bastard to avoid paying royalties and licensing fees for their bootleg of the album \"Sacro\" (with different titles and cover art).', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/0XUs-drwOXYhWN5zwF4ZFGfrv62xkI6J3PMbsAfr7sE/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:253/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTMxNDQx/MC0xNDEyOTE1NjQz/LTc5NDQuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-23 09:39:01', '2026-03-23 09:39:01'),
(40, 'Oasis', 'Ficha editorial armada para Oasis con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Noel Gallagher, Liam Gallagher, Andy Bell (2), Joey WaronkerAlias / variaciones: Noel Gallagher, O.A.S.I.S., Oas*s, The BandContexto de catalogoRock band from Burnage, Manchester, formed in 1991 out of the ashes of a band called The Rain (consisting of [a605785], [a605786], [a429260] and Chris Hutton on vocals) who started in 1990. Chris was sacked and [a53887] took over on vocals. His brother [a5452] (former guitar roadie for Inspiral Carpets\' Clint Boon) then joined as songwriter and additional guitarist.\r\nIn 1999, two of the founding members (Guigsy and Bonehead) left the group and Noel played their parts on the fourth album. Two new musicians were recruited - [a447669] and [a80566] - initially for touring duties, but became full-time and were part of the songwriting process on the following albums.  \r\nOn August 28, 2009, Noel announced that he was leaving the band after an altercation with Liam. The remaining members continued performing as Beady Eye before splitting up in 2014 while Noel formed [a2384642]. \r\nOn 27 August 2024, Oasis announced that they would reform for live performances in 2025.\r\nShort after this announcement their record company re-released some of their work (e.g. 30th anniversary edition \"Definitely Maybe\", 7\"-Boxes, ...).\r\n\r\nMembers:\r\nPaul McGuigan (1991-1999)\r\nPaul Arthurs (1991-1999)\r\nLiam Gallagher (1991-2009)\r\nTony McCarroll (1991-1995)\r\nNoel Gallagher (1991-2009)\r\nAlan White (2) (1995-2004)\r\nGem Archer (1999-2009) ex-Heavy Stereo\r\nAndy Bell (2) (1999-2009) ex-Ride & Hurricane #1\r\nZak Starkey: Drums (2004-2008) son of Ringo Starr\r\nChris Sharrock (2008-2009) ex-The La\'s\r\n\r\nNotable session & live members:\r\nScott McLeod (1995 Briefly replaced Guigsy; appears in Wonderwall video) ex-The Ya Ya\'s\r\nMatt Deighton: Lead Guitar & Backing Vocals (stood-in for Noel during non-UK dates) (2000) \r\nSteve White (3): Drummer (stood-in for brother Alan when he was ill) (2001)\r\nMike Rowe: Keyboards (1997-2002, also plays on Noel\'s solo work)\r\nJay Darlington (ex-Kula Shaker): Keyboards (2002-2009)\r\nTerry Kirkbride (ex-Proud Mary & Ambershades): Drums (2004, 2006-2007)\r\nJohnny Depp Guitar (1997)', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/_18ZXQ0IUmI_HI3On6HkLF6CHaJoaFrPxn2EnnVvXvE/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:799/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTE0MDE0/MC0xNzI0Nzk2MTMx/LTU3NzIuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-27 12:30:38', '2026-03-27 12:30:38'),
(41, 'Motörhead', 'Ficha editorial armada para Motörhead con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Larry Wallis, Eddie Clarke, Pete Gill, Brian RobertsonAlias / variaciones: Motor Head, MotorHead, Motorhead, MotrheadContexto de catalogoMotörhead were an English rock band formed in June 1975 by bassist, singer, and songwriter Ian Fraser Kilmister (1945–2015), professionally known by his stage name Lemmy, who had remained the sole constant member. The band are often considered a precursor to, or one of the earliest members of, the New Wave of British Heavy Metal, which re-energised heavy metal in the late 1970s and early 1980s. Despite this, Lemmy had always dubbed their music as simply \"rock and roll\".\r\n\r\nTo its end, Motörhead had released twenty-three studio albums, ten live recordings, twelve compilation albums and five EPs. Usually a power trio, they had particular success in the early 1980s with several successful singles in the UK Top 40 chart. The albums Overkill, Bomber, Ace of Spades, and particularly No Sleep \'til Hammersmith, cemented Motörhead\'s reputation as a top-tier rock band. As of 2012, Motörhead have sold more than 15 million albums worldwide.\r\n\r\nMotörhead are typically classified as Rock N Roll by Lemmy and band members, and their fusion of punk rock into the genre helped to pioneer speed metal and thrash metal. Their lyrics typically covered such topics as war, good versus evil, abuse of power, promiscuous sex, substance abuse, and, most famously, gambling. The name \"Motörhead\" is a reference to users of the drug amphetamine. The band\'s distinctive fanged-face logo, with its oversized boar\'s tusks, chains, and spikes, was created by artist Joe Petagno in 1977 for the cover of the Motörhead album and has appeared in many variations on covers of ensuing albums. The fanged face has been referred to variously as \"War-Pig\" and \"Snaggletooth\". The band is ranked number 26 on VH1\'s 100 Greatest Artists of Hard Rock.\r\n\r\nWhen Lemmy Kilmister died in December 2015, Mickey Dee declared that Motörhead (officially) is disbanded. No more tours or albums will be made. Only the brand will survive for the future.\r\n \r\nLast line-up:\r\nIan \"Lemmy\" Kilmister (vocals, bass 1975-2015)\r\nPhil \"Zoomster\" Campbell (guitar, 1984-2015)\r\nMickey Dee (drums, 1992-2015)\r\n\r\nPast members:\r\nMatt Sorum (touring drummer, 2009) \r\nTommy Aldrigde (In studio recording most of the \'March Or Die\' album, 1992)\r\nMichael \"Wurzel\" Burston (guitar, 1984-95)\r\nPhil \"Philthy Animal\" Taylor (drums, 1975-84 / 1987-92)\r\nPete Gill (drums, 1984-87)\r\nBrian Robertson (guitar, 1982-83)\r\n\"Fast\" Eddie Clarke (guitar, 1976-82)\r\nLarry Wallis (guitar, 1975-76)\r\nLucas Fox (drums, 1975)\r\n\r\nWinner of 1 Grammy Award:\r\n- Best Metal Performance for Whiplash from [m780782]', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/lRB1iRVXIDS5asXpGYJuLupb1mU1U-zhZx9I0zSvT0U/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:390/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTIzMzY1/OC0xNzA1NDMwMTc5/LTQ4NzIucG5n.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-29 10:31:16', '2026-03-29 10:31:16'),
(42, 'Blackfoot', 'Ficha editorial armada para Blackfoot con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Ken Hensley, Mark Woerpel, Neal Casal, Charlie HargrettAlias / variaciones: ブラックフットContexto de catalogoClassic Southern rock band that formed in 1969 as \"Fresh Garbage\" in Jacksonville, Florida. They changed their name to \"Hammer\" but changed it again in 1970 after hearing about another band with the same name. Blackfoot was then born. The following years were up and down for the band as members changed.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/L8_wCOGLmS516mMjluLEJlx1S4o93ll2yuloPfGf0sc/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:450/w:391/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTMyODYw/NS0xMTQ3MDU1MzQ1/LmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-29 15:03:24', '2026-03-29 15:03:24'),
(43, 'The Verve', 'Ficha editorial armada para The Verve con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Richard Ashcroft, Simon Jones, Nick McCabe, Simon TongAlias / variaciones: Verve, 神韻合唱團Contexto de catalogoThe Verve were an English rock band that formed in Wigan in 1990.\r\nCore members: Richard Ashcroft (vocals), Nick McCabe (guitar), Simon Jones (bass), and Peter Salisbury (drums). Simon Tong was added as second guitarist for the album \"Urban Hymns\" but not included in the group\'s 2008 reformation.\r\n\r\nGroup formed simply as Verve in 1991 (they became The Verve in 1994 after a dispute with the jazz label Verve).  Early material tended toward guitar-based soundscapes influenced by My Bloody Valentine, but they would later become a more conventional alt-rock group.\r\n\r\nIn April 1999 The Verve announced that they had mutually agreed to disband. 8 years later the original band reconciled their differences and reunited to record a new album and resume touring.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/pA_BNyhCOjB5xSbfY5uQo4_DD4LSSe2PFPPB9leYKKQ/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:444/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTEwMzU5/LTE2MDE4MTk5NTEt/NjEwNC5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-29 15:03:31', '2026-03-29 15:03:31'),
(44, 'The Smashing Pumpkins', 'Ficha editorial armada para The Smashing Pumpkins con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Billy Corgan, James Iha, Melissa Auf Der Maur, Jimmy ChamberlinAlias / variaciones: SP, Smashing Pumpkins, Smashingpumpkins, The Smashing PampkinsContexto de catalogoAlternative Rock (Modern Rock) band from Chicago, Illinois (USA).\r\n\r\nSmashing Pumpkins formed in 1988 by Billy Corgan and James Iha. The band split in 2000, but was reformed by Corgan in 2006.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/7N4O2Lf4sovfPYngOkAio34H7A8BNTygXmwpSRhlXBU/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:397/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI4OTcw/LTE2NDY4NTQzNDEt/ODc3Ny5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-30 12:20:06', '2026-03-30 12:20:06'),
(45, 'Sui Generis', 'Ficha editorial armada para Sui Generis con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Charly Garcia, Nito Mestre, Rinaldo Rafanelli, Francisco PrattiAlias / variaciones: Siu Generis, Sui GenerisContexto de catalogoFolk-prog rock band from Buenos Aires, Argentina, active from 1969 to 1975 (there was a short \"nostalgic\" reunion in 2000-2001).\r\nOne of the most Important groups in the Argentine rock scene from the 70s, enjoying enormous success and popularity during the first half of the decade, and a following that lasts until today throughout South America.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/URZeXMfgiJCxdah2f7ZSIx9tl3b3-KTdUT0kQ9HzkCU/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:391/w:400/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTIzNTQy/MDMtMTMxMjEyMDk0/MC5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-30 12:32:43', '2026-03-30 12:32:43'),
(46, 'Pearl Jam', 'Ficha editorial armada para Pearl Jam con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Eddie Vedder, Mike McCready, Matt Cameron, Matt ChamberlainAlias / variaciones: Peal Jam, Pearl, The Pearl Jam, 「珍珠果醬」 合唱團Contexto de catalogoAlternative Rock (Modern Rock) band from Seattle, Washington (USA), formed from the ashes of Jeff and Stone\'s previous band Mother Love Bone and the Temple of the Dog tribute project. Inducted to the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2017.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/ePBwuOV5mTRhks6owHP634F0kLsXoq-BH05NQWEZDR4/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:538/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTE3NTM5/NS0xNzEyOTU2ODky/LTg5MTkucG5n.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-30 16:08:14', '2026-03-30 16:08:14'),
(47, 'Accept', 'Ficha editorial armada para Accept con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Michael Wagener, Herman Frank, Uwe Lulis, Udo DirkschneiderAlias / variaciones: להקת לקבל, アクセプト, 容, 억셉트Contexto de catalogoGerman heavy metal band from the town of Solingen, originally assembled in the early 1970s by vocalist Udo Dirkschneider.\r\n\r\nTheir beginnings can be traced back to the late 1960s, when the band got its start under the name Band X. Accept\'s lineup has changed over the years, which has included different singers, guitarists, bassists and drummers. Accept have broken up and reformed multiple times. They first split up in 1989, several months after the release of Eat the Heat (which was their only album with Dirkschneider\'s initial replacement David Reece), but reformed in 1992 and released three more albums before disbanding again in 1997. After briefly reuniting in 2005, Accept announced their third reunion in 2009, with former T.T. Quick frontman Mark Tornillo replacing Dirkschneider.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/AQRONsIlMMNf_ScgyxdyTV5MxzkkqwFmMolWd9HdvU0/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:494/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI3MTQ3/NS0xNDI4OTUyODIy/LTc1MDMuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-30 16:08:17', '2026-03-30 16:08:17'),
(48, 'Siouxsie and the Banshees', 'Ficha editorial armada para Siouxsie and the Banshees con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Robert Smith, John McGeoch, Kenny Morris, Steven SeverinAlias / variaciones: A Banshees Production, Banshee, Banshees, SATBContexto de catalogoU.K. band, formed in London in 1976, fronted by Siouxsie Sioux (Susan Janet Ballion) on vocals, with Steven Severin (Steven John Bailey) playing bass. Kenny Morris played drums from July 1977 to September 1979. He left the Band famously together with then Guitarist John McKay a few hours before a concert of the \'Join Hands\' Tour after a heavy disagreement about signing records at a local store in Aberdeen. In 1980 Budgie (Peter Clarke) joined them on drums, up to their demise. He also worked with Siouxsie as the band The Creatures). Guitarists for the band have included Marco Pirroni (1976), Pete Fenton (1976-1977), John McKay (1977-1979), John McGeoch (1980-1982), John Valentine Carruthers (1984-1987), Jon Klein (1987-1995), Knox Chandler (1995, 2003) and also Robert Smith of The Cure (1980, 1982-1984) (who also worked with Severin as the band The Glove). Multiinstrumentalist Martin McCarrick was the band\'s full-time keyboard player from 1987 onwards. SATB disbanded in April 1996 and returned once for The Seven Year Itch tour in 2002. In 2003, [a893562] published Siouxsie & The Banshees: The Authorised Biography.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/uu5tXINV21tjS65RhVp8Oat1wFrVdQJCZhPt5sLl9yo/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:396/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTgwNTAx/LTE3NDQ0MDE5Njct/NjQxOC5wbmc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 08:39:04', '2026-03-31 08:39:04'),
(49, 'Arch Enemy', 'Ficha editorial armada para Arch Enemy con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Michael Amott, Daniel Erlandsson, Sharlee D&#039;Angelo, Angela GossowAlias / variaciones: アーク・エネミーContexto de catalogoA melodic death metal band from Halmstad, Sweden, founded by Michael Amott in 1995.\r\n\r\nCurrent line-up:\r\nMichael Amott - Lead Guitar (1995– )\r\nDaniel Erlandsson - Drums (1996, 1998– )\r\nSharlee D\'Angelo - Bass (1998– )\r\nJoey Concepcion - Lead Guitar (2023– )\r\nLauren Hart - Vocals (2026– )', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/NIQ1CLENMlQ9YgKy-cePZ1rPIirXVNWmtMTI8kiQR2M/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:399/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI1MjMy/My0xNzcxNzY3Nzc4/LTQzMjguanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 08:41:32', '2026-03-31 08:41:32'),
(50, 'Radiohead', 'Ficha editorial armada para Radiohead con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Thom Yorke, Jonny Greenwood, Phil Selway, Colin GreenwoodAlias / variaciones: Radio Head, Radiohead (Samples), Radioheads, レディオヘッドContexto de catalogoElectronic and alternative rock (modern rock) band from Oxfordshire, England (United Kingdom).\r\n\r\nThe name Radiohead comes from the Talking Heads song, \"Radio Head\", from the \"True Stories\" album.\r\n\r\nFormed by school friends in 1985, Radiohead did not release their first single until 1992\'s \"767600\". The cathartic \"Creep\", from the debut album \"Pablo Honey\" (1993), became a worldwide hit as grunge music dominated radio airwaves.\r\n\r\nRadiohead were initially branded as a one-hit wonder abroad, but caught on at home in the UK with their second album, \"The Bends\" (1995), earning fans with their dense guitar atmospheres and front man Thom Yorke\'s expressive singing. The album featured the hits \"High & Dry\", \"1463625\" and \"Fake Plastic Trees\".\r\n\r\nThe band\'s third album, \"OK Computer\" (1997), propelled them to greater attention. Popular both for its expansive sound and themes of modern alienation, the album has been acclaimed by critics as a landmark record of the 1990s, some critics go as far to consider it one of the best of all time. \"Kid A\" (2000) marked further evolution, containing influences from experimental electronic music.\r\n\r\n\"Hail To The Thief\" (2003) was seen as a conventional return to the guitar and piano-led rock sound. After fulfilling their contract with EMI, Radiohead released \"In Rainbows\" (2007) famously via a pay-what-you-want model. Their latest album,  \"A Moon Shaped Pool\", was released in May 2016.\r\n \r\nRadiohead\'s original influences were cited as alternative rock and post-punk bands like The Smiths, Pixies, Magazine, Joy Division and Siouxsie & The Banshees, who Thom Yorke claims inspired him to become a performer, and R.E.M. (with lead singer of the band, Thom Yorke, referring to himself as an \'R.E.M. groupie\').\r\n\r\nBand members:\r\nThom Yorke – vocals, guitar, piano, keyboards, laptop (1985–present)\r\nColin Greenwood – bass guitar (1985–present)\r\nEd O\'Brien – guitar, effects, backing vocals (1985–1990, 1990–present)\r\nPhilip Selway – drums, percussion (1985–present)\r\nJonny Greenwood – guitar, keyboards, ondes Martenot, glockenspiel, laptop, orchestral arrangements (1988–present)\r\n\r\nCurrent live members:\r\nClive Deamer – drums, percussion (2011–present)\r\n\r\nFormer members:\r\nRasmus \"Raz\" Peterson – tenor saxophone, alto saxophone (1985–1989)\r\nLiz Cotton – alto saxophone (1988–1989)\r\nCharlotte Cotton – alto saxophone (1988–1989)\r\nNigel Powell – drums (1990)\r\n\r\nPrevious names:\r\nOn a Friday (1985–1990, 1990–1991)\r\nShindig (1990)', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/eG3bUGOvNZSm8nRHMz3xf4tRfaxTz5sq9PpfsEMdTSY/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:500/w:500/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTM4NDAt/MTM4NjM1MjI4NS04/ODIyLmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 08:59:12', '2026-03-31 08:59:12'),
(51, 'Poison', 'Ficha editorial armada para Poison con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Richie Kotzen, C.C. DeVille, Bret Michaels, Blues SaracenoAlias / variaciones: Paris, Poison, ボイズン, ポイズンContexto de catalogoHair / Glam Metal (Heavy Metal) band from Mechanicsburg, Pennsylvania (USA).\r\n\r\nPoison is well known for their success in the mid 1980s to early 1990s.\r\nA few iconic songs by Poison are \'\'Nothin\' But a Good Time\'\'\r\nand \'\'Every Rose Has Its Thorn\'\', which both appeared on the album [m94324].\r\n\r\nFan club: [a6958177]\r\n\r\nMatt Smith of [a4221863] was a member of Poison before they got signed.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/sqlzN1-NM4NTv8MfI4ZuAYUhTcnZC0LIa0vBtJVcaMg/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:765/w:561/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI1NTI5/Mi0xNDM4NDc0NzEy/LTY2MzkucG5n.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 09:42:17', '2026-03-31 09:42:17'),
(52, 'Rainbow', 'Ficha editorial armada para Rainbow con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Roger Glover, Cozy Powell, Dave Rosenthal, Tony CareyAlias / variaciones: Blackmore&#039;s Rainbow, Blackmore&#039;s Raising, Rainbows, Richie Blackmore&#039;s RainbowContexto de catalogoRainbow (also known as Ritchie Blackmore\'s Rainbow or Blackmore\'s Rainbow) are a British rock band led by guitarist [a309402]. Established in 1975. \r\n\r\nBy 1973, Blackmore had steered [a170355] through a significant personnel change, with [a349634] and [a123906] being replaced by [a369909] and [a267270]. However, the new members were keen to add new musical styles and Blackmore found his request to record the Steve Hammond-penned \"Black Sheep of the Family\" with \"Sixteenth Century Greensleeves\" turned down by the band. He decided to record the song with [a291557] instead, using Dio\'s band [a312415] as additional musicians. He enjoyed the results, and a full album, billed as Ritchie Blackmore\'s Rainbow was recorded between February and March 1975 at Musicland Studios in Munich, Germany. The band name was inspired by the Rainbow Bar and Grill in Hollywood.\r\n\r\nAfter the release of three studio albums and an extensive world tour in 1977–78, Blackmore decided that he wanted to take the band in a new commercial direction away from the \"sword and sorcery\" theme. Dio did not agree with this change and left Rainbow. Together with then new vocalist [a353675], Blackmore scored a hit single with “Since You Been Gone”. \r\n\r\nAfter more lineup changes and albums, Ritchie disbanded Rainbow in early 1984 to rejoin the reunited Deep Purple.\r\n\r\nHe resurrected Rainbow once again in early 1994, just after leaving Deep Purple for good. However, Blackmore turned his attention to his long-time musical passion, Renaissance and medieval music. Rainbow was put on hold once again after playing its final concert in Esbjerg, Denmark in 1997. Blackmore, together with his partner [a485494] as vocalist then formed the Renaissance-influenced [a298038]. \r\n\r\nAgainst all expectations, Blackmore reformed Rainbow, with an all-new line-up, in late 2015. Blackmore announced that he would play \"all rock\" concerts in the summer of 2016 under the banner of \'Ritchie Blackmore\'s Rainbow\', his first rock shows since 1997. The new Rainbow line-up was announced on November 6, 2015. It featured [a4778506] singer [a4290197], [a324356] keyboardist [a309710], Blackmore’s Night drummer David Keith and bassist Bob Nouveau (Bob Curiano).', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/Wfj2wzV2Zvcajxz430CVppyUWvqBP3smmJVfqWwlJV0/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:505/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI0NTY0/OC0xMjU1ODc3MTM0/LmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 10:06:33', '2026-03-31 10:06:33'),
(53, 'Ratt', 'Ficha editorial armada para Ratt con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: John Corabi, Stephen Pearcy, Robbin Crosby, Warren DeMartiniAlias / variaciones: Rat, Ratt = ラット, ラットContexto de catalogoHair / Glam Metal (Heavy Metal) band from San Diego, California (USA).\r\n\r\nThe name Ratt came into being in the beginning of the 1980s, although the band\'s roots can be traced back to the mid \'70s and the band Mickey Ratt, which was fronted by vocalist Stephen Pearcy.  By 1983, after cycling through a number of different musicians and relocating to Los Angeles, where they would play a large part in the growing glam scene, the \"classic\" line-up of Pearcy, guitarists Warren DiMartini and Robbin \"King\" Crosby, bassist Juan Croucier, and drummer Bobby \"Blotz\" Blotzer was in place.  From 1984 through 1990, the band would record and release 5 commercially successful albums.  By the turn of the decade, though, the band\'s fortunes were declining as popular tastes in music were changing and Crosby, once one of the driving forces in the band, found himself mired in a heroin addiciton that ultimately led to his removal from Ratt.  After substituting guitarist Michael Schenker for Crosby for touring purposes, Ratt released what would be the final single of their initial run, \"Nobody Rides for Free\" (from the soundtrack for the movie \"Point Break\") in 1991 as a four-piece.  The following year, Pearcy and DiMartini left the band, effectively ending Ratt.\r\n\r\nIn 1997, the members met to discuss the possibility of a reunion.  Croucier declined to join and it was decided that Crosby was in no condition to participate (still suffering from drug addiction, the guitarist was severely overweight and HIV positive, a fact he would publicly disclose in 2001; he would die of a heroin overdose the following year).  Robbie Crane was brought in to replace Croucier and Pearcy would occasionally handle second guitar duties.  This line-up released a self-titled album in 1999 but it did not have the same commercial success as their previous releases.  Pearcy left the band the following year and began touring as \"Ratt featuring Stephen Pearcy\".  This led to lawsuit over right to the name \"Ratt\" between the singer and Blotzer and DiMartini, from which the latter two emerged victorious, although the issue of the rights to the name remains a point of contention for all the surviving members of the classic line-up.   \r\n\r\nBlotzer and DiMartini would tour throughout the first half of the 2000s under the Ratt banner with several different vocalists and second guitarists before reuniting with Pearcy in 2006.  In 2009, the band, with Robbie Crane still playing bass and former Quiet Riot guitarist Carlos Cavazo on board, recorded the well-received LP \"Infestation\".  However, owing to tensions between the members, the band announced that it would be going on indefinite hiatus the following year.  In 2012, Crane announced that he was no longer a part of Ratt.  Shortly thereafter, it was announced that Juan Croucier had returned to the group.  In the spring of 2014, Pearcy announced that he was leaving the band again, citing unresolved personal and business tensions.  In the summer of 2015, both Bobby Blotzer and Juan Croucier launched separate touring projects for the purpose of performing Ratt songs, with Blotzer stating the DiMartini refused to participate in any Ratt-related touring unless it included Pearcy and Croucier.  In late 2015, the drummer announced that his touring band was now the official version of Ratt.  Blotzer brought legal action against Croucier for touring as \"Ratt\'s Juan Croucier\" while DiMartini brought action against Blotzer for using the Ratt name.  In November 2016, the courts ruled that the Ratt name still belonged to the surviving members of Ratt\'s original partnership which was created in 1985.  With the announcement of this ruling, Pearcy, DiMartini, and Croucier announced that they were reuniting under the Ratt banner and expelled Blotzer from the partnership.  In 2018, Pearcy and Croucier announced that they were touring with an entirely new set of musicians, stating that DeMartini expressed a disinterest in participating.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/JiuOUTDhLCtuMsUaNlyFqZHx3XGGWV3gwlDg3jWKg8w/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:303/w:454/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI2NDg1/My0xNDMyOTkxMzUz/LTY0MjkuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 10:06:41', '2026-03-31 10:06:41'),
(54, 'Billy Idol', 'Ficha editorial armada para Billy Idol con señales cruzadas de DiscogsAlias / variaciones: B Idol, B, Idol, B.  Idol, B. IbolContexto de catalogoBritish post punk/hard rock musician, songwriter, and artist. \r\n\r\nBorn: 30 November 1955 in Stanmore, London, England, UK. \r\n\r\nIdol first achieved fame as a founding member (with Tony James) of London punk rock band Generation X (4), starting in 1976 and disbanded in 1981. Later he embarked on a successful solo career and after releasing his second studio album \"29809\" (1983), became an international rock star, and moved to the US to pursue his career. \r\n\r\nHis music videos are also known for their constant playback on the nascent television network MTV.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/Zr_mQN793E-YuzkB_OLPK3D1dCfC7dbU7tynMvs4hWs/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:486/w:490/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTQ2Mzcz/LTE2MTMwNjY1ODMt/ODg0Ni5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 10:21:29', '2026-03-31 10:21:29'),
(55, 'Dokken', 'Ficha editorial armada para Dokken con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Mark Boals, Reb Beach, Don Dokken, George LynchAlias / variaciones: Don Dokken, ドッケン, 도켄Contexto de catalogoHair / Glam Metal (Heavy Metal) band from Los Angeles, California (USA).\r\n\r\nDokken formed in 1976.The band disbanded in 1989 and reformed in 1993.\r\n\r\nCurrent line-up\r\nChris McCarvill: Bass\r\nDon Dokken: Vocals\r\nBJ Zampa: Drums\r\nJon Levin: Guitar\r\n\r\nFormer/Past members\r\nMick Brown: Drums\r\nJeff Pilson: Bass\r\nMichael Delaouglou (aka Mikkey Dee): Drums\r\nGreg Leon: Guitar \r\nGreg Pecka: Drums\r\nJuan Croucier: Bass\r\nReb Beach: Guitar\r\nAlex De Rosso: Guitar\r\nJohn Norum: Guitar\r\nGeorge Lynch: Guitar  \r\nBarry Sparks: Bass\r\nMark Boals: Bass, Backing Vocals', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/KQbbTJMYi3N6hDRVz0R787hqIyOif3MN8G-m239VRUw/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:518/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTI4NjMz/MS0xNTcyNDczODQ3/LTk3NDUuanBlZw.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 10:33:20', '2026-03-31 10:33:20'),
(56, 'The Rolling Stones', 'Ficha editorial armada para The Rolling Stones con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Mick Jagger, Keith Richards, Ian Stewart, Ron WoodAlias / variaciones: Die Rolling Stones, Les Glimmer Twins, Les Rolling Stones, Los Rolling StonesContexto de catalogoEnglish rock band formed in London in May 1962. They are one of the longest-lived and most commercially successful groups in rock history. Inducted into the Rock And Roll Hall of Fame in 1989 (Performer).\r\n\r\nBand members\r\n\r\n05/1962 - 05/1963\r\n[a255182] (Keyboards, piano)\r\n\r\n05/1962 - 06/1969\r\n[a409290] (Lead and rhythm guitars)\r\n\r\n06/1962 - 10/1962\r\n[a414255] (Bass)\r\n\r\n06/1962 - 12/1962\r\n[a677434] (Drums)\r\n\r\n06/1962 - present\r\n[a90541] (Lead vocals, harmonica, percussion)\r\n[a166570] (Lead and rhythm guitars, acoustic guitar, backing vocals)\r\n\r\n12/1962 - 01/1993\r\n[a272814] (Bass)\r\n\r\n01/1963 - 08/2021\r\n[a299325] (Drums and percussion)\r\n\r\n07/1969 - 12/1974\r\n[a300117] (Lead and slide guitars)\r\n\r\n03/1975 - present\r\n[a271311] (Guitars, backing vocals)\r\n\r\n60s UK discography\r\nRolling Stones (same as US England\'s Newest Hitmakers except a few songs)\r\nRolling Stones No2 (not released in the US market)\r\nOut Of Our Heads (different track listing than the US version)\r\nAftermath (different track listing than the US version)\r\nBig Hits (High Tide And Green Grass) (different track listing than the US version)\r\nHave You Seen Your Mothe LIVE! (only made for export to Scandinavia)\r\nBetween The Buttons (different track listing than the US version)\r\nFlowers (only made for export to Europe)\r\nTheir Satanic Majesties Request\r\nBeggars Banquet\r\nLet It Bleed\r\nThrough The Past Darkly (different track listing than the US version)\r\n\r\n60s US discography\r\nEnglands Newest Hitmakers (same as UK The Rolling Stones except a few songs)\r\n12x5 (not issued in the UK)\r\nNOW! (not issued in the UK)\r\nOut Of Our Heads (different track listing than the UK version)\r\nDecembers Children (exclusive US release)\r\nAftermath (different track listing than the UK version)\r\nBig Hits (High Tide And Green Grass) (different track listing than the UK version)\r\nGot LIVE If You Want It! \r\nBetween The Buttons (different track listing than the UK version)\r\nFlowers\r\nTheir Satanic Majesties Request\r\nBeggars Banquet\r\nLet It Bleed\r\nThrough The Past Darkly (different track listing than the UK version)', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/H3bmFFLnkb4qDTzFQtLRbvMjBNs8bR8R7Zz0JJcMP14/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:690/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTIwOTkx/LTE2NTY5NjI2MTUt/OTA3Ny5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 10:33:33', '2026-03-31 10:33:33'),
(57, 'Los Suaves', 'Ficha editorial armada para Los Suaves con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Alberto Cereijo, Carlos Domínguez, Yosi Domínguez, Hermes Alogo MebuyAlias / variaciones: SuavesContexto de catalogoSpanish hard rock band founded in 1979 by brothers Domínguez: Yosi Domínguez (vocals, harmonica, guitar) & Charly Domínguez (bass), Alberto Cereijo (lead guitar, 1991-present), Fernando Calvo (rhythm guitar, 2000-present), Tino Mojón (drums, 2002-present).', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/An6xBl1oyFQ3KlWEZjonfRkCrfItHd8n4308DXnR-BU/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:213/w:237/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTMyNjI3/NDctMTY4ODM4MzAz/OC00Mjg0LmpwZWc.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 13:55:08', '2026-03-31 13:55:08'),
(58, 'Rage Against the Machine', 'Ficha editorial armada para Rage Against the Machine con señales cruzadas de DiscogsMiembros relacionados: Tom Morello, Zack de La Rocha, Brad Wilk, Tim CommerfordAlias / variaciones: R.A.T.M, R.A.T.M., RATM, RageContexto de catalogoAmerican alternative / funk metal / modern rock band formed in 1991 in Los Angeles, California (often abbreviated as RATM, R.A.T.M. or shortened to Rage). They are noted for their blend of hip hop, heavy metal, punk and funk as well as their revolutionary politics and lyrics. They split up in October 2000 after Zack de la Rocha decided to leave the band for a solo career, the rest of the members of the band joined Audioslave (formed by Soundgarden\'s frontman Chris Cornell). After seven years of absence, Rage Against The Machine reunited in 2007 for a number of shows. In 2017, the band members other than Zack de la Rocha formed the supergroup Prophets of Rage with Public Enemy\'s Chuck D and DJ Lord and Cypress Hill\'s B-Real. After the announcement of RATM\'s return in 2019, Prophets Of Rage was disbanded, although the band\'s second reunion ended in January 2024.', NULL, 'https://i.discogs.com/OU7oo1YnluHTBjvEnPyKgjikyLxZk_JfamdnmEFIhBg/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:418/w:600/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9BLTEyMjEy/LTE1NjAyMjIwOTgt/OTU4OC5qcGVn.jpeg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Discogs', '2026-03-31 14:24:47', '2026-03-31 14:24:47');
